dataElements.description: WHO defines a Buruli ulcer case as any person with painless nodule, papule, plaque or oedema evolving into a painless ulcer with undermined edges, often leading to invalidating sequelae in an endemic area.
dataElements.formName: Number of new BU cases diagnosed within reporting year
